1246
01:07:20,744 --> 01:07:22,162
IS going to happen
to my husband.

1247
01:07:22,246 --> 01:07:24,122
(COUGHING)

1248
01:07:43,767 --> 01:07:47,145
Did you ever use
a wishing well as a child?

1249
01:07:49,356 --> 01:07:51,191
Throw a coin in the water

1250
01:07:51,316 --> 01:07:55,445
and pray with all your heart.

1251
01:07:58,448 --> 01:08:01,243
Some water is magic.

1252
01:08:12,129 --> 01:08:15,716
Before there was a house

1253
01:08:16,258 --> 01:08:17,593
or a pool...

1254
01:08:18,427 --> 01:08:21,430
<i>there was a spring
in the ground.</i>

1255
01:08:22,347 --> 01:08:24,182
<i>I don't know
what's beneath the surface.</i>

1256
01:08:24,266 --> 01:08:26,018
<i>Maybe no one does.</i>

1257
01:08:27,019 --> 01:08:31,857
<i>But I know it gives us
our deepest desires.</i>

1258
01:08:31,982 --> 01:08:36,236
<i>The people then
must have worshipped it</i>

1259
01:08:36,361 --> 01:08:39,781
when they found out
what it could do.

1260
01:08:42,034 --> 01:08:43,785
<i>Temagami.</i>

1261
01:08:44,995 --> 01:08:47,289
The deep water.

1262
01:08:48,332 --> 01:08:51,752
WHISPERING VOICES:
<i>Temagami. Temagami.</i>

1263
01:08:51,835 --> 01:08:54,630
MRS. SUMMERS: The
well has a wish of its own.

1264
01:08:54,713 --> 01:08:58,759
<i>Once the water is woken,
it will take a life.</i>

1265
01:08:58,884 --> 01:09:02,888
<i>Someone has to pay
so the water can keep giving.</i>

1266
01:09:03,013 --> 01:09:04,890
<i>The way it gave to me.</i>

1267
01:09:07,059 --> 01:09:09,436
Tommy was so sick.

1268
01:09:11,855 --> 01:09:13,690
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1269
01:09:13,815 --> 01:09:15,233
And look at him now.

1270
01:09:20,322 --> 01:09:22,866
But what happened
to your daughter?

1271
01:09:22,991 --> 01:09:24,743
It was...

1272
01:09:24,826 --> 01:09:27,663
better with Rebecca,

1273
01:09:27,746 --> 01:09:30,666
more humane for a child

1274
01:09:30,749 --> 01:09:32,042
not to know

1275
01:09:33,126 --> 01:09:34,920
what was coming.

1276
01:09:36,088 --> 01:09:37,422
Mom! Help!

1277
01:09:37,506 --> 01:09:40,092
(IN DISTANCE)
Mom! Mom!

1278
01:09:41,051 --> 01:09:44,221
(REBECCA SCREAMING)
(COUGHING)

1279
01:09:44,346 --> 01:09:45,639
REBECCA: Mom!

1280
01:09:45,764 --> 01:09:47,808
Becky? Becky!

1281
01:09:47,891 --> 01:09:50,185
(SCREAMS) Mom! Mom!

1282
01:09:50,268 --> 01:09:52,270
Help! (SCREAMS)
(TOMMY COUGHING)

1283
01:09:52,396 --> 01:09:53,855
TOMMY:
Mom, Becky's outside!

1284
01:09:53,980 --> 01:09:55,941
Mom! Mom!

1285
01:09:57,234 --> 01:09:59,111
REBECCA: (SCREAMS) Mom!

1286
01:09:59,236 --> 01:10:01,822
TOMMY: Mom,
Becky's outside!

1287
01:10:01,947 --> 01:10:05,200
MRS. SUMMERS:
<i>The water used me as a vessel</i>

1288
01:10:05,325 --> 01:10:08,120
<i>to do what must be done.</i>

1289
01:10:09,454 --> 01:10:11,832
<i>Don't worry about your husband.</i>

1290
01:10:12,958 --> 01:10:15,877
He's the one who gets the wish.

1291
01:10:16,169 --> 01:10:17,337
He gets his health.

1292
01:10:17,462 --> 01:10:19,089
I got my son back.

1293
01:10:19,214 --> 01:10:21,174
It'll be worth it.

1294
01:10:21,299 --> 01:10:22,801
You'll see.

1295
01:10:22,884 --> 01:10:26,054
Love requires sacrifice.

1296
01:10:26,138 --> 01:10:28,306
That's not love.

1297
01:10:29,683 --> 01:10:33,103
It's not a sacrifice
if you get something back.

1298
01:10:33,895 --> 01:10:36,440
Rebecca asked where you were.

1299
01:10:37,899 --> 01:10:39,901
She's still looking for you.

1300
01:10:39,985 --> 01:10:42,070
You can still help us.

1301
01:10:42,154 --> 01:10:45,282
There has to be
some way to stop this.

1302
01:10:48,994 --> 01:10:52,831
(COUGHING)

1303
01:10:58,712 --> 01:11:00,797
(GASPING AND COUGHING)

1304
01:11:00,922 --> 01:11:03,008
(WATER BURBLING)

1305
01:11:18,523 --> 01:11:20,400
(WHEEZING)

1306
01:11:22,360 --> 01:11:24,613
(CHUCKLING OMINOUSLY)

1307
01:11:26,948 --> 01:11:29,701
It'll be over soon.

1308
01:11:31,244 --> 01:11:34,664
The water will sleep again.

1309
01:11:37,501 --> 01:11:39,544
And...

1310
01:11:39,669 --> 01:11:42,464
someone else
will find the house.

1311
01:11:43,965 --> 01:11:48,637
Someone else who needs its help.

1312
01:12:05,070 --> 01:12:07,113
(GASPING AND GAGGING)

1313
01:12:26,216 --> 01:12:28,218
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

1314
01:12:37,644 --> 01:12:39,688
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

1315
01:12:41,606 --> 01:12:43,942
IZZY: Thanks, Ronin.
See you tomorrow.

1316
01:12:45,110 --> 01:12:46,528
(DOOR OPENS)

1317
01:12:46,653 --> 01:12:48,655
ELLIOT: Hey, Mom, Dad,
we're home.

1318
01:12:48,780 --> 01:12:50,323
(KEYS JINGLING)

1319
01:12:51,408 --> 01:12:52,742
Mom?

1320
01:12:54,870 --> 01:12:56,538
Dad, we're home.

1321
01:13:00,166 --> 01:13:02,127
She's not answering.

1322
01:13:02,836 --> 01:13:04,796
Think Dad might be with her.

1323
01:13:05,547 --> 01:13:07,215
I'm gonna go check the garage.

1324
01:13:18,476 --> 01:13:20,520
(CAT MEOWS)

1325
01:13:22,063 --> 01:13:24,107
(SETS GLASS DOWN) Cider?

1326
01:13:36,119 --> 01:13:37,454
Cider?

1327
01:13:42,334 --> 01:13:44,169
Come here, Cider.

1328
01:13:55,013 --> 01:13:56,598
(SMACKING LIPS)

1329
01:13:58,058 --> 01:13:59,601
Come here, Cider.

1330
01:14:12,948 --> 01:14:14,532
What?

1331
01:14:17,035 --> 01:14:18,912
(CAT MEOWS)
(COLLAR BELL JINGLING)

1332
01:14:21,706 --> 01:14:23,458
(CAT MEOWS)
(COLLAR BELL JINGLING)

1333
01:14:24,459 --> 01:14:26,002
Cider?

1334
01:14:27,420 --> 01:14:28,797
(COLLAR BELL JINGLING)

1335
01:14:28,922 --> 01:14:30,131
(CAT MEOWS)

1336
01:14:36,221 --> 01:14:38,264
(CREAKING)

1337
01:14:39,432 --> 01:14:40,809
(CAT MEOWS)

1338
01:14:40,892 --> 01:14:42,143
It's okay, buddy.

1339
01:14:42,769 --> 01:14:44,104
I'm right here.

1340
01:14:47,565 --> 01:14:49,192
(CAT WHIMPERS)

1341
01:14:52,112 --> 01:14:53,989
(CLICKING AND CREAKING)

1342
01:14:54,114 --> 01:14:56,199
(POOL THRUMMING)

1343
01:15:07,877 --> 01:15:09,671
(GRUNTING)

1344
01:15:16,302 --> 01:15:18,096
(GRUNTING)

1345
01:15:20,849 --> 01:15:22,434
Cider?

1346
01:15:22,517 --> 01:15:23,935
(SNARLS)

1347
01:15:24,060 --> 01:15:25,353
(SCREAMS)

1348
01:15:29,065 --> 01:15:30,984
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1349
01:15:31,109 --> 01:15:33,862
(MUFFLED YELLING)

1350
01:15:37,073 --> 01:15:38,408
IZZY: Elliot!

1351
01:15:42,620 --> 01:15:45,749
Elliot! Elliot!

1352
01:15:48,376 --> 01:15:50,462
(GRUNTING)

1353
01:15:58,344 --> 01:16:00,013
(EVE YELLS)
Mom.

1354
01:16:00,096 --> 01:16:01,973
Come on. Okay, okay.
Izzy, help me. Come on.

1355
01:16:02,057 --> 01:16:04,976
(BOTH GRUNTING
AND STRAINING)

1356
01:16:09,189 --> 01:16:11,524
(GRUNTING)

1357
01:16:11,608 --> 01:16:12,901
I don't know what happened.

1358
01:16:12,984 --> 01:16:14,384
I don't know...
Elliot's down there.

1359
01:16:14,444 --> 01:16:15,629
All I know is that he...
Go in the house.

1360
01:16:15,653 --> 01:16:17,072
Call for help. Go!
Okay.

1361
01:16:17,155 --> 01:16:18,823
Okay, I'm going.

1362
01:16:30,085 --> 01:16:31,586
Dad! (GRUNTS)

1363
01:16:34,047 --> 01:16:36,049
(COUGHING AND PANTING)

1364
01:16:44,015 --> 01:16:46,017
(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

1365
01:17:01,991 --> 01:17:03,284
(GRUNTS)

1366
01:17:06,037 --> 01:17:08,206
(HYPERVENTILATING)

1367
01:17:15,171 --> 01:17:16,339
(WHIMPERS)

1368
01:17:17,674 --> 01:17:19,425
(GLASS CLINKS ON FLOOR)

1369
01:17:25,014 --> 01:17:27,100
(CREAKING)
(GASPS)

1370
01:17:38,319 --> 01:17:39,320
Dad?

1371
01:17:45,660 --> 01:17:47,704
(FLOORBOARDS CREAKING)

1372
01:17:54,919 --> 01:17:56,963
(THUDDING)
(GASPS)

1373
01:17:57,046 --> 01:17:58,590
Dad!

1374
01:17:58,715 --> 01:18:00,091
RAY: There you are.

1375
01:18:01,384 --> 01:18:03,052
I've been looking for you, Iz.

1376
01:18:03,178 --> 01:18:04,679
(WATER TRICKLING)

1377
01:18:04,804 --> 01:18:06,097
What's the matter?

1378
01:18:06,222 --> 01:18:08,308
(IZZY WHIMPERING)

1379
01:18:12,896 --> 01:18:14,856
(WET FOOTSTEPS SLOSHING)
(WHIMPERING)

1380
01:18:14,981 --> 01:18:16,524
(FOOTSTEPS STOP)

1381
01:18:18,735 --> 01:18:21,696
Okay, I'm...
I... I'm calling for help.

1382
01:18:26,409 --> 01:18:27,952
Don't do that!
(SCREAMS)

1383
01:18:28,036 --> 01:18:29,704
(IZZY GASPS AND SCREAMS)

1384
01:18:29,787 --> 01:18:32,165
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1385
01:18:48,723 --> 01:18:50,391
(YELPS)
RAY: I know you want me

1386
01:18:50,475 --> 01:18:52,018
to get better.

1387
01:18:53,311 --> 01:18:54,896
You understand, don't you?

1388
01:18:56,856 --> 01:18:58,650
We have to get help.

1389
01:18:58,733 --> 01:19:01,027
Baby, we already got help.

1390
01:19:03,738 --> 01:19:05,823
Life is too hard for Elliot.

1391
01:19:06,532 --> 01:19:07,867
It's better this way.

1392
01:19:10,578 --> 01:19:12,121
Ahh! (GRUNTS)

1393
01:19:12,247 --> 01:19:13,915
(SCREAMS)

1394
01:19:15,750 --> 01:19:17,043
(SHRIEKS)

1395
01:19:19,003 --> 01:19:20,755
(SCREAMS)

1396
01:19:23,132 --> 01:19:25,969
Help! Help! Help!

1397
01:19:26,511 --> 01:19:27,679
Marco.

1398
01:19:27,762 --> 01:19:29,764
(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

1399
01:19:54,372 --> 01:19:56,541
(DISTORTED VOICES HOWLING)

1400
01:19:58,626 --> 01:19:59,961
(SNARLS)

1401
01:20:01,796 --> 01:20:03,381
(SHRIEKING)

1402
01:20:18,187 --> 01:20:20,106
(PANTING)

1403
01:20:21,024 --> 01:20:22,483
Help!

1404
01:20:22,692 --> 01:20:25,028
(POUNDING CONTINUES)
Please! Help!

1405
01:20:25,153 --> 01:20:27,488
Is anyone out there?
Call for help!

1406
01:20:27,572 --> 01:20:29,741
(PANTING)

1407
01:20:36,456 --> 01:20:37,957
RAY: Marco.

1408
01:20:43,880 --> 01:20:45,548
(STATIC BUZZES)
(SCREAMS)

1409
01:20:45,631 --> 01:20:49,302
MAN: (SINGING)
<i>Take me out to the ball game</i>

1410
01:20:49,427 --> 01:20:53,181
<i>Take me out with the crowd</i>

1411
01:20:53,306 --> 01:20:56,684
<i>Buy me some peanuts
and Cracker Jack</i>

1412
01:20:56,809 --> 01:20:58,478
<i>I don't care...</i>

1413
01:20:58,561 --> 01:21:00,730
(STATIC DRONING)

1414
01:21:03,775 --> 01:21:06,903
You're supposed to say "Polo."
(SCREAMS)

1415
01:21:20,583 --> 01:21:22,960
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

1416
01:21:23,086 --> 01:21:24,587
(MUFFLED WHIMPERING)

1417
01:21:41,646 --> 01:21:43,648
(SERENE MUSIC PLAYING)

1418
01:22:17,640 --> 01:22:20,017
(GASPING)

1419
01:22:26,607 --> 01:22:30,027
Why don't you stay here,
and it'll all be over soon.

1420
01:22:30,945 --> 01:22:32,822
(LOCK CLICKS)

1421
01:22:32,947 --> 01:22:35,032
(BREATHING RAGGEDLY)

1422
01:22:39,162 --> 01:22:41,247
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1423
01:22:43,082 --> 01:22:45,585
(EVE GASPS AND PANTS)

1424
01:22:45,710 --> 01:22:47,044
Ellie.

1425
01:22:48,921 --> 01:22:50,673
Oh, God. Come on.

1426
01:22:50,798 --> 01:22:51,966
Come on, Ellie. Come on.

1427
01:22:52,091 --> 01:22:54,969
One, two, three, four, five.

1428
01:22:55,052 --> 01:22:56,846
Come on. Come on.

1429
01:22:56,971 --> 01:22:59,390
(PANTING)

1430
01:22:59,515 --> 01:23:01,350
(SOBBING)

1431
01:23:01,434 --> 01:23:02,435
RAY: It's too late.

1432
01:23:02,518 --> 01:23:04,770
(PANTING)

1433
01:23:05,521 --> 01:23:07,398
Love requires sacrifice.

1434
01:23:07,482 --> 01:23:09,025
Ray.

1435
01:23:09,984 --> 01:23:11,444
Oh, Ray, please.

1436
01:23:11,569 --> 01:23:13,821
Please, we need
to get him to a hospital, Ray.

1437
01:23:13,905 --> 01:23:16,324
He needs your help.
Look at him.

1438
01:23:16,407 --> 01:23:17,408
(GRUNTS)
(GASPS)

1439
01:23:19,952 --> 01:23:21,996
(RAY BREATHING HEAVILY)

1440
01:23:22,121 --> 01:23:23,414
(EVE GRUNTS)

1441
01:23:23,539 --> 01:23:26,042
The water chose him.

1442
01:23:28,085 --> 01:23:29,837
He loves the pool.

1443
01:23:29,921 --> 01:23:31,881
Elliot will always be here.

1444
01:23:32,006 --> 01:23:33,591
He'll always be here.

1445
01:23:35,009 --> 01:23:37,428
(YELLING)
(GRUNTING)

1446
01:23:37,512 --> 01:23:38,638
(RAY COUGHS)

1447
01:23:38,763 --> 01:23:41,015
(YELLS)
(GROANS AND COUGHS)

1448
01:23:47,396 --> 01:23:48,856
(GROANS)

1449
01:23:48,981 --> 01:23:50,858
(WATER BURBLING)

1450
01:23:50,983 --> 01:23:52,818
(HIGH-PITCHED RINGING)

1451
01:23:52,944 --> 01:23:54,237
IZZY: <i>Dad.</i>

1452
01:23:54,362 --> 01:23:56,072
(GURGLING)

1453
01:23:56,155 --> 01:23:57,907
<i>Something has you.</i>

1454
01:23:58,991 --> 01:24:00,535
<i>You have to fight it.</i>

1455
01:24:00,660 --> 01:24:02,203
(GROANS)

1456
01:24:02,328 --> 01:24:03,829
DOCTOR: <i>It's going
to take sacrifice,</i>

1457
01:24:03,955 --> 01:24:05,998
<i>but you can have
a good life together.</i>

1458
01:24:06,082 --> 01:24:08,334
EVE: <i>I just need to know
that you want that, too.</i>

1459
01:24:08,417 --> 01:24:10,127
<i>Please come back.</i>

1460
01:24:10,211 --> 01:24:11,462
RAY: <i>I want that, too.</i>

1461
01:24:11,546 --> 01:24:12,713
IZZY: <i>Elliot needs you.</i>

1462
01:24:13,047 --> 01:24:15,508
(HIGH-PITCHED RINGING
CONTINUES)

1463
01:24:15,591 --> 01:24:17,176
Ray?

1464
01:24:17,260 --> 01:24:18,886
Come back.

1465
01:24:18,970 --> 01:24:21,138
Come back. Come back.
(RETCHING)

1466
01:24:21,222 --> 01:24:22,932
(GASPS)
(RAY GROANS)

1467
01:24:23,474 --> 01:24:25,518
(GRUNTS AND COUGHS)

1468
01:24:25,601 --> 01:24:27,562
(PANTING)

1469
01:24:30,815 --> 01:24:31,941
RAY: Izzy, no...

1470
01:24:33,359 --> 01:24:35,027
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1471
01:24:38,614 --> 01:24:40,074
It's me.

1472
01:24:40,199 --> 01:24:41,576
I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry.

1473
01:24:41,701 --> 01:24:43,327
ELLIOT:
Mom. (COUGHS)

1474
01:24:43,411 --> 01:24:45,246
EVE: Ellie!
Is he okay?

1475
01:24:45,329 --> 01:24:48,624
He's breathing. We
gotta get him out of here.

1476
01:24:49,709 --> 01:24:52,420
Come on. Come on,
baby. (GROANING)

1477
01:24:53,796 --> 01:24:55,256
IZZY: Dad, come on.
Let's go.

1478
01:24:55,339 --> 01:24:56,674
(GROANING)

1479
01:24:56,799 --> 01:24:58,759
WHISPERING VOICES:
<i>Temagami.</i>

1480
01:24:58,843 --> 01:25:01,345
(WHOOSHING)

1481
01:25:01,470 --> 01:25:03,806
(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

1482
01:25:08,686 --> 01:25:11,105
(ELLIOT GROANING)
IZZY: Dad?

1483
01:25:11,188 --> 01:25:12,898
Oh, my God. Mom?

1484
01:25:13,024 --> 01:25:15,109
(GROANING)

1485
01:25:15,234 --> 01:25:16,986
(COUGHING AND CHOKING)

1486
01:25:17,111 --> 01:25:18,654
EVE: Baby, what's wrong?

1487
01:25:20,323 --> 01:25:22,033
Elliot.
Mom, it's the water.

1488
01:25:22,116 --> 01:25:24,397
It's not gonna let him leave.
(EVE GASPING AND WHIMPERING)

1489
01:25:24,452 --> 01:25:26,245
EVE: Ray, it's...
It's getting worse.

1490
01:25:26,370 --> 01:25:28,289
(ELLIOT COUGHING)

1491
01:25:28,372 --> 01:25:31,000
EVE: Get him up, Izzy.
Help me.

1492
01:25:32,460 --> 01:25:34,170
Someone has to pay.

1493
01:25:37,673 --> 01:25:40,092
(RAY GASPS DEEPLY)

1494
01:25:43,721 --> 01:25:46,974
(ALL CLAMORING)
(VOICE WHEEZING)

1495
01:25:51,062 --> 01:25:53,356
(WATER SPLASHING) (ELLIOT
COUGHING AND GASPING)

1496
01:25:54,482 --> 01:25:55,524
IZZY: Dad?

1497
01:25:58,194 --> 01:25:59,403
Dad, where are you going?

1498
01:25:59,487 --> 01:26:00,821
Don't look back.

1499
